summary: A really simple little house a tad south of Ivarstead.
descriptionHtml:
My first Skyrim mod, and hopefully not the last. Something small. If you have any comments or suggestions, please tell me. We can all learn from one another.

It's well... a house. In Ivarstead. I guess it's a rest stop I suppose? Oh, and it's lore-friendly. Sure. Once upon a time there was this guy. He built a house, only to subsequently die. Murdered by a duck, tripped on a pebble and got stabbed by a twig in the eye. Not sure, don't care, but he let YOU, yes YOU, the dragonborn, have his house.

Still, don't mess with ducks. They WILL get back at you. The guy who built that place learnt the hard way.

Have at it. There shouldn't be any conflicts since it uses all vanilla objects. Oh, and all my screenshots are from the CK. My computer but a simple laptop I received three years ago, and while I'm building my computer, I only have four parts.

Really quick FAQ:

-"Where is it?"

Tad bit to the south of Ivarstead. I said Ivarstead four times already, including the title. Can you not read?

-"IT'S SO CRAMPED AND TINY HOW CAN I FIT MY DOVAKIIN'S EGO IN THIS SMALL PLACE?"

It's meant to be tiny. This is my first mod.

-"MARI U SUK STAP MAKIN MADS"

No.

---
author: MissMarifire
